# Authentication, DB Encryption & CSV Import

Three features to add to the portfolio tracker: local authentication, encryption of the SQLite database at rest, and CSV import from Avanza, Nordnet, and Binance.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Authentication model**: This plan uses a **single local user** with password-based authentication (no registration page). The password is set on first launch via a setup screen. This keeps it simple for a personal portfolio tracker. If you want multi-user support or OAuth, let me know.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **DB Encryption key source**: The encryption key will be **derived from the user's password** (via PBKDF2). This means changing the password requires re-encrypting the database. An alternative would be a separate encryption passphrase stored in an env variable — let me know your preference.

> [!WARNING]
> **Breaking change**: Switching from `better-sqlite3` to `better-sqlite3-multiple-ciphers` replaces the native addon. The existing unencrypted `portfolio.db` will need a one-time migration to an encrypted format. The plan includes a migration script for this.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Feature 1: Authentication

The project already has `passport`, `passport-local`, `express-session`, and `memorystore` in `package.json` but none of them are wired up. We'll activate them.

#### Architecture

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser
    participant Express
    participant Session Store
    participant SQLite

    Browser->>Express: POST /api/auth/login {password}
    Express->>SQLite: Look up user record
    SQLite-->>Express: {passwordHash, salt}
    Express->>Express: Verify bcrypt hash
    Express->>Session Store: Create session
    Express-->>Browser: 200 + Set-Cookie

    Browser->>Express: GET /api/holdings (with cookie)
    Express->>Session Store: Validate session
    Session Store-->>Express: OK
    Express->>SQLite: Query holdings
    Express-->>Browser: 200 + JSON
```

---

#### [NEW] [server/auth.ts](file:///c:/projects/portfolio-tracker/server/auth.ts)

New module that encapsulates all authentication logic:

- **`users` table** schema (id, username, passwordHash) — single-row table
- **`setupAuth(app)`** function:
  - Configures `express-session` with `memorystore` (already a dependency)
  - Configures `passport` with `passport-local` strategy
  - Registers routes:
    - `POST /api/auth/setup` — first-time password creation (only if no user exists)
    - `POST /api/auth/login` — login with password
    - `POST /api/auth/logout` — destroy session
    - `GET /api/auth/me` — returns current user or 401
  - Exports `requireAuth` middleware for protecting API routes
- Password hashing via Node.js built-in `crypto.scrypt` (no new dependency needed)

#### [MODIFY] [schema.ts](file:///c:/projects/portfolio-tracker/shared/schema.ts)

- Add `users` table definition:
  ```ts
  export const users = sqliteTable("users", {
    id: integer("id").primaryKey({ autoIncrement: true }),
    username: text("username").notNull().default("admin"),
    passwordHash: text("password_hash").notNull(),
    salt: text("salt").notNull(),
    createdAt: text("created_at").notNull(),
  });
  ```

#### [MODIFY] [storage.ts](file:///c:/projects/portfolio-tracker/server/storage.ts)

- Add `users` table to `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` block
- Add `getUser()`, `createUser()` methods to `IStorage` and implementation

#### [MODIFY] [index.ts](file:///c:/projects/portfolio-tracker/server/index.ts)

- Import and call `setupAuth(app)` before `registerRoutes()`

#### [MODIFY] [routes.ts](file:///c:/projects/portfolio-tracker/server/routes.ts)

- Add `requireAuth` middleware to all `/api/*` routes (except auth routes)

