### Feature 3: CSV Import (Avanza, Nordnet, Binance)

#### Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[Upload CSV] --> B{Detect Format}
    B -->|Avanza| C[Parse Avanza]
    B -->|Nordnet| D[Parse Nordnet]
    B -->|Binance| E[Parse Binance]
    C --> F[Normalize to internal format]
    D --> F
    E --> F
    F --> G[Preview Table]
    G --> H{User maps unknowns}
    H --> I[Create assets/holdings/transactions]
```

The existing `POST /api/parse-transaction` endpoint is too limited (single line, no file upload). We'll build a proper CSV import pipeline.

---

#### [NEW] [server/importers/index.ts](file:///c:/projects/portfolio-tracker/server/importers/index.ts)

Main importer orchestrator:
- Accepts raw CSV string + source type (`avanza` | `nordnet` | `binance`)
- Auto-detects format if source not specified (by checking header row)
- Delegates to source-specific parser
- Returns normalized `ImportRow[]`

#### [NEW] [server/importers/avanza.ts](file:///c:/projects/portfolio-tracker/server/importers/avanza.ts)

Parses Avanza CSV export:

| Avanza Column | Maps to |
|---|---|
| `Datum` | `date` |
| `Konto` | `account` |
| `Typ av transaktion` | `type` (Köp→buy, Sälj→sell, Utdelning→dividend, etc.) |
| `Värdepapper/beskrivning` | `assetName` |
| `Antal` | `quantity` |
| `Kurs` | `price` |
| `Belopp` | `amount` |
| `Courtage` | `fees` (may be a separate row — handled) |
| `Valuta` | `currency` |
| `ISIN` | `isin` |

- Handles Swedish number format (comma decimal, space thousands)
- Handles Swedish date format (`YYYY-MM-DD`)
- Semicolon delimiter (`;`)

#### [NEW] [server/importers/nordnet.ts](file:///c:/projects/portfolio-tracker/server/importers/nordnet.ts)

Parses Nordnet CSV export:

| Nordnet Column | Maps to |
|---|---|
| `Datum` | `date` |
| `Transaktionstekst` / `Transaktionstyp` | `type` |
| `Värdepapper` | `assetName` |
| `ISIN` | `isin` |
| `Antal` | `quantity` |
| `Kurs` | `price` |
| `Belopp` | `amount` |
| `Kurtage` | `fees` |
| `Valuta` | `currency` |

- Also semicolon-delimited
- Swedish number format
- Column names may vary by language setting (Swedish/Norwegian/Danish) — we handle Swedish

#### [NEW] [server/importers/binance.ts](file:///c:/projects/portfolio-tracker/server/importers/binance.ts)

Parses Binance Spot Trade History CSV:

| Binance Column | Maps to |
|---|---|
| `Date(UTC)` | `date` |
| `Market` / `Pair` | Split into `baseAsset` + `quoteAsset` (e.g., `BTC/USDT` → BTC) |
| `Type` | Side (`BUY`/`SELL`) |
| `Price` | `price` |
| `Amount` | `quantity` |
| `Total` | `amount` |
| `Fee` | `fees` |
| `Fee Coin` | `feeCurrency` |

- Comma-delimited CSV
- Period decimal separator
- Needs asset mapping: `BTCUSDT` → asset "Bitcoin", type "crypto", currency "USD"
- The mapping table maps known Binance symbols to our asset types

#### [NEW] [server/importers/types.ts](file:///c:/projects/portfolio-tracker/server/importers/types.ts)

Shared types:
```ts
export interface ImportRow {
  source: "avanza" | "nordnet" | "binance";
  date: string;              // ISO YYYY-MM-DD
  type: "buy" | "sell" | "dividend" | "deposit" | "withdrawal" | "fee" | "transfer";
  assetName: string;
  ticker?: string;
  isin?: string;
  quantity?: number;
  price?: number;
  amount: number;
  fees: number;
  currency: string;
  account?: string;          // e.g., "Avanza ISK"
  rawLine: string;           // original CSV line for audit
  warnings: string[];        // parsing warnings
}

export interface ImportResult {
  rows: ImportRow[];
  unmappedAssets: string[];  // names not found in existing assets
  errors: string[];
  source: string;
}
```

